5724206.png' alt=\"wx_sys\" width=\"300\" height=\"232\" \/><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-413\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">system deployment configuration<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The first diagram show the &#8220;parts&#8221; of the system abstracted as UML components. \u00a0The second diagram illustrates a deployment configuration of the components interconnected across their interfaces.<\/p>\n<p>The system uses an interface based upon MQ Telemetry Transport (MQTT) message brokering.<\/p>\n<p>The host stores recordings in a cloud data base. This is a nice example of the <em>Internet of Things<\/em>.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_424\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-424\" style=\"width: 219px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/onefact.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/stevenson_screen.png\"><img alt='stevenson_screen-219x300-1287837' class=\"wp-image-424 size-medium\" src='https:\/\/onefact.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/stevenson_screen-219x300-1287837.png' alt=\"stevenson_screen\" width=\"219\" height=\"300\" \/><\/a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-424\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Stevenson Screen<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This model provides a functional allocation for a weather system known as a Stevenson Screen. \u00a0Such a weather enclosure contains and protects instrumentation used to measure temperature, humidity, barometric pressure and records specialized derivatives of these measurements. A barometer, hygrometer, thermometer, psychrometer and dewcell measure physical factors in the environment. \u00a0A thermograph records temperature and [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":413,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[5],"tags":[6,7,8],"class_list":["post-1083","post","type-post","status-publis